NETHERLANDS: Dutch state lowers price for new bond to 100.30.Dutch state lowers price for new bond to 100.30.The Finance Ministry set today's opening price for tap sales of the Dutch government's new 5.75 percent bond due September 2002 at 100.30.Tap sales of the new bond opened on Monday at a price of 100.60 but this was later lowered to 100.40.Tap sales will continue daily from 07.00 GMT to 15.00 GMT until further notice.-- Amsterdam newsroom +31 20 504 5000